60|$|Alice could see, {{as well as}} if {{she were}} looking over their shoulders, that all the jurors were writing down 'stupid things!' on their slates, and <b>she</b> <b>could</b> <b>even</b> make out that one of them didn't know how to spell 'stupid,' and that he had to ask his {{neighbour}} to tell him. 'A nice muddle their slates'll be in before the trial's over!' thought Alice.|$|E
